page.title: 19ECOLOGY-3
page.content:
{3.WATER MEADOWS}Water meadows cover quite a large part of the area and many damp loving plants can be found here. They include bullrushes, reeds of different types, watercress, and marsh marigolds. Water birds such as coots, ducks and moorhens can be seen and water voles and foxes are common.
{4.ROUGHLAND}These areas of coarse, long grass hide many small mammals, insects and birds. A large variety of different plants grow in a jumble. Roughland tends to look very wild but it is often the home of more plants and animals than the other areas.
